H0.text: The Free Officers Movement was composed of young junior army officers committed to unseating the monarchy of which African country. South Africa

H1.text: The Free Officers Movement was composed of young junior army officers committed to unseating the monarchy of which African country. Morocco

H2.text: The Free Officers Movement was composed of young junior army officers committed to unseating the monarchy of which African country. Libya

H3.text: The Free Officers Movement was composed of young junior army officers committed to unseating the monarchy of which African country. EGY

A4.text: The Free Officers movement was a group of Arab nationalist and Nasserist officers in the Libyan Army that planned and carried out the 1969 Libyan revolution, which overthrew the Senussi monarchy of King Idris I.

A5.text: All but one of them studied at the military academy and did not go to university.
